parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line corrosion and leak can cause brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Brake line rusted through
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

symptoms: Brake failure
sudden stop
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal sticks to the floor
brake pedal does not return to its normal position
brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure

brake vibration

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake light failure can cause accidents or rear-end collisions, which can result in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Brake lights do not function
brake lights are not illuminated
brake lights are dim or flickering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety-critical systems to malfunction, including brake lights, hazard lights, and turn signals, which can lead to accidents or increase the risk of injury.
symptoms: Intermittent or complete failure of brake lights
hazard lights
and turn signals; flickering or burning smell from electrical components; smoke rising from the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or increase the risk of injury.
symptoms: Brake lights not functioning or functioning intermittently; faulty brake light switch; brake lights not illuminating when the brake pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and become stranded, which can lead to accidents or increase the risk of injury.
symptoms: Engine stalling; engine stopping and not restarting; electrical system still functioning
but engine not starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun visor can cause obstruction of the driver's view, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The sun visor falls off or breaks
obstructing the driver's view
dangling by a wire
or failing to stay in the closed position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake lights do not illuminate
brake pedal feels sticky or spongy
brake lights suddenly stop working
turn signals and brake lights do not work together.
